1
00:00:01,001 --> 00:00:04,212
<i>A hostage situation is currently unfolding</i>

2
00:00:04,295 --> 00:00:07,132
<i>at the famous and exclusive</i>
<i>island destination,</i>

3
00:00:07,215 --> 00:00:09,050
<i>La Playa Roja.</i>

4
00:00:09,759 --> 00:00:13,680
<i>We just heard the news.</i>
<i>Two of the escaped hostages are now dead.</i>

5
00:00:13,763 --> 00:00:17,642
<i>- Who?</i>
<i>- A Jules Santos and a Mama Ona Chan.</i>

6
00:00:17,726 --> 00:00:19,477
[WENDY] <i>Olsen, what happened to Liam?</i>

7
00:00:19,561 --> 00:00:21,187
- <i>Liam! Liam!</i>
<i>- Ma'am! Ma'am!</i>

8
00:00:21,980 --> 00:00:23,314
<i>What are you doing, Ma?</i>

9
00:00:23,398 --> 00:00:26,317
<i>You might have wounds</i>
<i>and just not be telling me.</i>

10
00:00:26,401 --> 00:00:28,778
<i>I promise, I'm not hurt.</i>

11
00:00:28,862 --> 00:00:30,697
<i>I'm okay, thanks to Sir Magnus.</i>

12
00:00:30,780 --> 00:00:32,657
<i>- Magnus?</i>
<i>- He saved me.</i>

13
00:00:32,741 --> 00:00:34,451
<i>He would've done the same for me.</i>

14
00:00:34,534 --> 00:00:36,911
<i>He reminds me of you.</i>
<i>He has a big heart.</i>

15
00:00:36,995 --> 00:00:38,538
<i>Thank you for saving Liam.</i>

16
00:00:38,621 --> 00:00:41,416
<i>- You didn't abandon us.</i>
<i>- Thank you too, sir.</i>

17
00:00:42,083 --> 00:00:43,960
[LENI] <i>Aren't we going home yet, Pa?</i>

18
00:00:44,043 --> 00:00:45,670
[EMIL]<i> You and your sister</i>
<i>can go home first.</i>

19
00:00:45,754 --> 00:00:47,672
<i>I need to finish my mission.</i>

20
00:00:47,756 --> 00:00:51,050
<i>Ayen's not with us on this island.</i>

21
00:00:51,134 --> 00:00:54,554
<i>She's here.</i>
<i>But your sister changed her mind again.</i>

22
00:00:54,637 --> 00:00:58,433
<i>But I have made up my mind.</i>
<i>I'm going to kill Magnus.</i>

23
00:00:58,516 --> 00:01:01,478
<i>After that, we will live a luxurious life</i>

24
00:01:01,561 --> 00:01:03,354
<i>just like the Rojas.</i>

25
00:01:07,275 --> 00:01:08,193
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

26
00:01:08,276 --> 00:01:10,779
Uh, nurse? I have a question.

27
00:01:10,862 --> 00:01:13,406
When do you think I can be discharged?

28
00:01:13,490 --> 00:01:15,825
Our companions have already left.

29
00:01:15,909 --> 00:01:20,455
You're not cleared for discharge yet.
Your blood pressure is elevated.

30
00:01:20,538 --> 00:01:21,956
Oh, all right.

31
00:01:22,040 --> 00:01:26,628
[JOY] Uh, ma'am? What about me?

32
00:01:26,711 --> 00:01:29,798
I just need to verify your records, ma'am.

33
00:01:29,881 --> 00:01:31,883
I'll get back to you.

34
00:01:31,966 --> 00:01:33,259
- [JOY] Thanks.
- Sige.

35
00:01:33,343 --> 00:01:36,930
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

36
00:01:37,514 --> 00:01:39,140
- [JOY] Ma'am?
- Hmm?

37
00:01:39,891 --> 00:01:41,768
We're still lucky, huh?

38
00:01:41,851 --> 00:01:44,145
We got out of that hellhole.

39
00:01:44,229 --> 00:01:45,230
Mm-hmm.

40
00:01:45,814 --> 00:01:48,650
Too bad Love didn't make it out with us.

41
00:01:48,733 --> 00:01:50,026
[GRUNTS SOFTLY]

42
00:01:50,110 --> 00:01:51,611
Oh, Love…

43
00:01:51,694 --> 00:01:53,655
And Smile--

44
00:01:53,738 --> 00:01:55,573
I mean, Leni.

45
00:01:55,657 --> 00:01:56,699
[JOY SIGHS HEAVILY]

46
00:01:57,784 --> 00:01:59,410
I hope the ground swallows her up.

47
00:01:59,494 --> 00:02:01,955
I wish. Damn that Smile.

48
00:02:02,038 --> 00:02:03,373
[JOY HUFFS]

49
00:02:05,166 --> 00:02:07,001
By the way, Joy,

50
00:02:07,085 --> 00:02:11,381
do you remember how
you accused me of being the traitor?

51
00:02:11,464 --> 00:02:12,507
Hmm?

52
00:02:13,883 --> 00:02:16,177
- Sorry, ma'am.
- "Sorry"?

53
00:02:16,261 --> 00:02:18,972
I think you're the reason
my blood pressure's elevated!

54
00:02:19,055 --> 00:02:22,308
But, ma'am, what about
Sir Liam and everyone else?

55
00:02:22,976 --> 00:02:24,644
Do you think they're okay?

56
00:02:25,228 --> 00:02:28,523
A-And are we really safe?

57
00:02:28,606 --> 00:02:32,402
Did you hear about
Ma'am Jules and her manager?

58
00:02:34,696 --> 00:02:39,701
But Doc Jessie and Ma'am Conney are fine.

59
00:02:39,784 --> 00:02:41,286
They were saved.

60
00:02:41,369 --> 00:02:43,955
And the police are all over Alicante.

61
00:02:44,038 --> 00:02:48,459
No one in their right mind
would attack us here.

62
00:02:48,543 --> 00:02:50,336
So you have nothing to fear.

63
00:02:50,420 --> 00:02:51,671
Okay?

64
00:02:52,589 --> 00:02:54,340
We're safe here.

65
00:02:54,424 --> 00:02:56,634
- [TENSE MUSIC SWELLS]
- [WOMEN SCREAM]

66
00:02:56,718 --> 00:02:57,844
- What--
- My apologies, ma'am.

67
00:02:57,927 --> 00:02:59,888
I'm the bodyguard of Mr. Maristella.

68
00:02:59,971 --> 00:03:01,681
[HAPPY SIGHS IN RELIEF, PANTS]

69
00:03:01,764 --> 00:03:03,600
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

70
00:03:06,644 --> 00:03:09,230
- Happy, Joy.
- Uh. [CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY]

71
00:03:09,314 --> 00:03:10,857
Hello, Senator.

72
00:03:10,940 --> 00:03:11,983
I'm Joy. Hello, Senator.

73
00:03:12,066 --> 00:03:13,610
I'm really glad you're both okay.

74
00:03:13,693 --> 00:03:16,821
I know you went through hell back there.

75
00:03:17,655 --> 00:03:19,365
But I have to ask…

76
00:03:22,076 --> 00:03:23,578
Did you see my son?

77
00:03:24,829 --> 00:03:25,997
Is he okay?

78
00:03:26,080 --> 00:03:32,128
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

79
00:03:32,211 --> 00:03:34,297
- Enough! [SOBS]
- [WHIP SNAPS]

80
00:03:34,380 --> 00:03:35,465
- [DADO GRUNTS]
- [WHIP SNAPS]

81
00:03:35,548 --> 00:03:36,799
[MACKY SCREAMS]

82
00:03:36,883 --> 00:03:37,842
Enough!

83
00:03:40,261 --> 00:03:42,013
We need him alive.

84
00:03:43,556 --> 00:03:45,934
[MACKY GRUNTS, GROANS]

85
00:03:47,560 --> 00:03:50,313
[SHOUTS]

86
00:03:51,314 --> 00:03:53,524
- [MACKY ON VIDEO] <i>Please…</i>
- [DADO] <i>Huh?</i>

87
00:03:53,608 --> 00:03:56,486
- [WHIP SNAPS]
- [AGONIZED SCREAM]

88
00:03:57,195 --> 00:04:01,157
This is enough
to warn anyone who tries to defy us.

89
00:04:02,617 --> 00:04:03,952
Sir Macky, Senator?

90
00:04:04,035 --> 00:04:06,079
Uh… [CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY] He's fine.

91
00:04:06,162 --> 00:04:09,457
If… If I remember correctly,

92
00:04:09,540 --> 00:04:14,504
he was at the restaurant dancing.

93
00:04:14,587 --> 00:04:17,215
We were all dancing along.

94
00:04:17,298 --> 00:04:19,425
Then he went off with his group.

95
00:04:19,509 --> 00:04:25,098
- I went back to the rest of the staff.
- Um… what group?

96
00:04:25,181 --> 00:04:27,350
The VIP hostages.

97
00:04:27,433 --> 00:04:28,685
Guests, Senator!

98
00:04:28,768 --> 00:04:29,686
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

99
00:04:29,769 --> 00:04:31,688
She meant to say, VIP guests, Senator.

100
00:04:31,771 --> 00:04:33,022
Yes, guests.

101
00:04:34,315 --> 00:04:38,152
So you're not sure if my son is safe?

102
00:04:38,236 --> 00:04:41,531
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

103
00:04:41,614 --> 00:04:42,907
Um…

104
00:04:42,991 --> 00:04:44,242
Senator,

105
00:04:45,410 --> 00:04:47,578
a lot of people were left behind.

106
00:04:47,662 --> 00:04:51,541
Maybe you could send some help?

107
00:04:52,917 --> 00:04:54,294
Senator…

108
00:04:56,462 --> 00:04:59,299
The hostage takers are ruthless.

109
00:04:59,799 --> 00:05:04,470
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

110
00:05:04,554 --> 00:05:07,265
- [SOBBING, SCREAMING]
- [WHIP SNAPS]

111
00:05:09,726 --> 00:05:12,395
[SOBS] <i>Oh my God!</i>

112
00:05:12,478 --> 00:05:14,105
<i>Oh my God!</i>

113
00:05:14,188 --> 00:05:15,315
[SCREAMS]

114
00:05:22,947 --> 00:05:29,912
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

115
00:05:59,233 --> 00:06:05,364
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

116
00:06:13,873 --> 00:06:17,001
[BOAT MOTOR HUMMING]

117
00:06:18,503 --> 00:06:24,383
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

118
00:06:32,350 --> 00:06:36,020
[HUMMING CONTINUES]

119
00:06:37,063 --> 00:06:42,860
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

120
00:06:42,944 --> 00:06:44,112
[PHONE BUZZING]

121
00:06:44,195 --> 00:06:51,119
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

122
00:06:51,202 --> 00:06:52,328
[GRUNTS]

123
00:06:54,080 --> 00:06:57,208
- [MACKY ON VIDEO] <i>Aah! Enough!</i>
- [CHUCKLES]

124
00:06:57,291 --> 00:07:01,003
<i>- Please! Enough!</i>
- [DADO] <i>Huh?</i>

125
00:07:02,839 --> 00:07:06,175
[PHONE RINGING, BEEPS]

126
00:07:07,218 --> 00:07:08,261
Boss Emil?

127
00:07:08,344 --> 00:07:10,471
Those cops won't quit.

128
00:07:10,555 --> 00:07:12,390
They won't leave the island.

129
00:07:12,473 --> 00:07:15,560
And more are coming.

130
00:07:15,643 --> 00:07:18,146
What do you want me to do?

131
00:07:18,229 --> 00:07:24,694
Ask the senator for 100 million
for Macky Maristella's life.

132
00:07:25,486 --> 00:07:30,408
To make up for the ransom
we won't get from the escaped VIPs.

133
00:07:30,491 --> 00:07:34,078
Boss Emil, don't forget about our deal.

134
00:07:34,954 --> 00:07:38,458
I won't just ask
Senator Maristella for money.

135
00:07:38,541 --> 00:07:42,545
You negotiate with him about that.

136
00:07:43,296 --> 00:07:47,133
What matters now is that we stop
the police from sending reinforcements,

137
00:07:47,216 --> 00:07:50,428
and that we get rid of the ones
still here on the island.

138
00:07:52,388 --> 00:07:57,226
Find a way to take care of
that nosy cop too.

139
00:07:57,310 --> 00:07:58,394
Yes, sir.

140
00:08:00,271 --> 00:08:06,277
[DARK MUSIC PLAYING]

141
00:08:08,237 --> 00:08:10,072
[NEWS ANCHOR] <i>According to the police,</i>

142
00:08:10,156 --> 00:08:13,409
<i>a rescue team has been deployed</i>
<i>to La Playa Roja.</i>

143
00:08:13,493 --> 00:08:18,372
<i>But we haven't received an update</i>
<i>regarding the hostages there.</i>

144
00:08:18,456 --> 00:08:22,126
<i>One of the hostages is the son</i>
<i>of Senator Eduardo Maristella,</i>

145
00:08:22,210 --> 00:08:23,961
<i>Macky Maristella.</i>

146
00:08:24,045 --> 00:08:25,046
[PHONE CHIMES]

147
00:08:25,129 --> 00:08:30,635
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

148
00:08:31,928 --> 00:08:33,179
Let's go, let's go.

149
00:08:33,262 --> 00:08:40,061
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

150
00:08:44,607 --> 00:08:46,150
We're severely undermanned, sir.

151
00:08:46,234 --> 00:08:47,485
Ammo is running low.

152
00:08:47,568 --> 00:08:49,403
Only nine of us are left.

153
00:08:49,487 --> 00:08:53,199
Estimated nine suspects
left on their side.

154
00:08:53,282 --> 00:08:55,368
They are armed with M4 rifles,

155
00:08:55,451 --> 00:08:57,078
M9 pistols,

156
00:08:57,161 --> 00:08:58,371
and hand grenades.

157
00:08:58,454 --> 00:09:02,416
How will you be able to evacuate
the civilians, Lieutenant?

158
00:09:02,500 --> 00:09:05,044
<i>We'll take them to where we docked, sir.</i>

159
00:09:05,795 --> 00:09:08,130
<i>We'll send the coordinates.</i>

160
00:09:08,214 --> 00:09:11,968
<i>But, sir, the area's</i>
<i>covered with explosives,</i>

161
00:09:12,051 --> 00:09:14,804
<i>trip wires, and landmines.</i>

162
00:09:14,887 --> 00:09:19,517
I sent Cariaso and Bautista
to check if the path is safe to use.

163
00:09:20,268 --> 00:09:21,143
<i>Sir,</i>

164
00:09:21,727 --> 00:09:25,523
<i>once evacuation is complete,</i>
<i>we need immediate reinforcement</i>

165
00:09:25,606 --> 00:09:27,858
<i>to neutralize the suspects.</i>

166
00:09:27,942 --> 00:09:30,570
Where is the senator's son?

167
00:09:30,653 --> 00:09:33,406
We saw Macky Maristella
during the encounter yesterday.

168
00:09:33,489 --> 00:09:35,283
But we weren't able to secure him.

169
00:09:35,366 --> 00:09:37,994
Can you confirm if he's still alive?

170
00:09:38,077 --> 00:09:42,206
<i>No, sir. We cannot confirm his condition.</i>

171
00:09:42,290 --> 00:09:43,708
[DOMINGO] <i>We may negotiate.</i>

172
00:09:43,791 --> 00:09:44,959
<i>But let me repeat,</i>

173
00:09:45,042 --> 00:09:48,462
<i>I will not agree to the demands</i>
<i>of the hostage takers.</i>

174
00:09:48,546 --> 00:09:50,298
Carry out your plan.

175
00:09:50,381 --> 00:09:53,384
Evacuate all civilians to safety.

176
00:09:53,467 --> 00:09:56,053
I'll send reinforcements immediately.

177
00:09:56,137 --> 00:09:57,013
Okay?

178
00:09:57,096 --> 00:09:58,180
Copy, sir.

179
00:09:58,264 --> 00:10:02,602
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

180
00:10:05,855 --> 00:10:07,940
With all due respect, Senator,

181
00:10:08,024 --> 00:10:10,401
you are not authorized to come in here.

182
00:10:10,484 --> 00:10:11,736
Have you seen this?

183
00:10:15,364 --> 00:10:17,116
[LUCAS] <i>Senator Maristella,</i>

184
00:10:17,199 --> 00:10:20,328
<i>do you still want to see your son alive?</i>

185
00:10:20,411 --> 00:10:21,704
<i>Of course you do.</i>

186
00:10:22,413 --> 00:10:29,211
<i>Then help us convince</i>
<i>that damn Major Domingo.</i>

187
00:10:29,295 --> 00:10:32,673
<i>Tell him to get rid of the police here,</i>

188
00:10:32,757 --> 00:10:35,509
<i>and not to send reinforcements.</i>

189
00:10:35,593 --> 00:10:37,386
So what are you planning to do?

190
00:10:38,596 --> 00:10:40,056
Senator Maristella.

191
00:10:41,599 --> 00:10:46,937
I can assure you we're doing
everything we can to save your son.

192
00:10:47,521 --> 00:10:49,398
But let me reiterate,

193
00:10:49,482 --> 00:10:53,819
we will not give in to the demands
of the hostage takers.

194
00:10:53,903 --> 00:10:59,158
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

195
00:10:59,241 --> 00:11:00,660
- [LIAM GRUNTS]
- Eat up, son.

196
00:11:02,078 --> 00:11:03,037
Mm.

197
00:11:04,163 --> 00:11:05,164
Mm…

198
00:11:05,873 --> 00:11:06,791
Have some.

199
00:11:06,874 --> 00:11:09,293
- Finish it, son.
- Ma.

200
00:11:09,377 --> 00:11:11,170
Please, I'm okay.

201
00:11:11,253 --> 00:11:15,091
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

202
00:11:15,174 --> 00:11:18,177
[INHALES, EXHALES DEEPLY]

203
00:11:18,260 --> 00:11:19,720
I know you're not, Ma.

204
00:11:21,013 --> 00:11:23,641
Lieutenant Areza said

205
00:11:23,724 --> 00:11:27,478
they're getting ready
to get us off this island.

206
00:11:27,561 --> 00:11:34,026
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

207
00:11:35,111 --> 00:11:36,404
Are you still mad?

208
00:11:37,488 --> 00:11:38,906
Or not?

209
00:11:41,242 --> 00:11:43,619
[LIAM]<i> Would you do anything</i>
<i>for your family?</i>

210
00:11:43,702 --> 00:11:45,746
<i>Even if it was wrong?</i>

211
00:11:46,831 --> 00:11:48,582
<i>What do you mean?</i>

212
00:11:49,708 --> 00:11:52,753
<i>What Mama did to Aunt Wendy…</i>

213
00:11:54,296 --> 00:11:55,840
<i>That was so wrong.</i>

214
00:11:57,383 --> 00:11:59,009
<i>But her reason for doing it</i>

215
00:12:00,469 --> 00:12:02,388
<i>was so she wouldn't be parted from me.</i>

216
00:12:04,849 --> 00:12:06,308
<i>Does that justify it?</i>

217
00:12:07,518 --> 00:12:09,019
<i>In my opinion, dude,</i>

218
00:12:10,521 --> 00:12:11,605
<i>it's still wrong.</i>

219
00:12:12,189 --> 00:12:15,901
<i>But maybe our perspective will change</i>

220
00:12:16,610 --> 00:12:18,529
<i>once we become parents ourselves.</i>

221
00:12:20,322 --> 00:12:23,284
What you did was wrong.

222
00:12:24,702 --> 00:12:25,828
So wrong.

223
00:12:27,788 --> 00:12:28,873
But, Ma…

224
00:12:31,292 --> 00:12:33,544
I can't stay mad at you for too long.

225
00:12:36,255 --> 00:12:38,132
No matter what you do…

226
00:12:42,178 --> 00:12:43,888
I'll still love you the same.

227
00:12:45,556 --> 00:12:49,727
[GRETA BREATHING SHAKILY]

228
00:12:51,061 --> 00:12:52,938
I love you too, son.

229
00:12:59,862 --> 00:13:01,530
There's so much happening, Ma.

230
00:13:04,033 --> 00:13:07,286
I don't know who to trust anymore.

231
00:13:10,247 --> 00:13:14,376
Can you believe that Smile,
a member of our staff,

232
00:13:15,503 --> 00:13:16,962
is Emil's child?

233
00:13:17,588 --> 00:13:20,508
I really think he's the leader
of this hostage taking.

234
00:13:22,301 --> 00:13:23,552
Leader?

235
00:13:24,220 --> 00:13:26,013
Emil? He's the leader?

236
00:13:26,680 --> 00:13:27,890
[SIGHS]

237
00:13:27,973 --> 00:13:29,433
Everything was planned out.

238
00:13:30,768 --> 00:13:32,269
Every detail.

239
00:13:39,068 --> 00:13:40,569
I almost forgot, Ma.

240
00:13:42,696 --> 00:13:44,490
What were you telling me earlier?

241
00:13:46,825 --> 00:13:49,411
Something about it being your fault.

242
00:13:51,080 --> 00:13:53,499
[GRETA WHISPERS]
<i>I didn't mean for this to happen.</i>

243
00:13:58,003 --> 00:14:00,172
[VOICE BREAKING] <i>It's all my fault.</i>

244
00:14:00,256 --> 00:14:01,590
<i>It's all my fault.</i>

245
00:14:01,674 --> 00:14:04,593
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC PLAYING]

246
00:14:06,845 --> 00:14:08,389
You were awake?

247
00:14:11,350 --> 00:14:12,726
What was your fault?

248
00:14:14,228 --> 00:14:15,604
I meant…

249
00:14:17,022 --> 00:14:19,775
what I did to your Aunt Wendy.

250
00:14:20,526 --> 00:14:22,403
But we're okay now.

251
00:14:22,486 --> 00:14:25,614
You said we're okay now, right?

252
00:14:28,367 --> 00:14:31,078
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

253
00:14:31,161 --> 00:14:34,790
[MELLOW MUSIC PLAYING]

254
00:14:34,874 --> 00:14:36,041
Good morning, dude.

255
00:14:37,877 --> 00:14:39,128
Morning.

256
00:14:39,753 --> 00:14:41,589
How are you feeling?

257
00:14:42,423 --> 00:14:43,549
I'm still alive.

258
00:14:44,341 --> 00:14:46,677
[BOTH CHUCKLE]

259
00:14:46,760 --> 00:14:48,137
Here, have some water.

260
00:14:48,220 --> 00:14:49,263
Drink up.

261
00:14:51,807 --> 00:14:52,933
Thank you.

262
00:14:53,017 --> 00:14:54,518
I have some good news, bro.

263
00:14:54,602 --> 00:14:55,561
Hmm?

264
00:14:55,644 --> 00:14:57,271
Lieutenant Areza said

265
00:14:57,354 --> 00:15:00,441
Joy and the others
safely reached Alicante.

266
00:15:00,524 --> 00:15:02,192
[LIAM EXHALES]

267
00:15:06,113 --> 00:15:08,490
- We really are the best tandem.
- [BOTH CHUCKLE]

268
00:15:10,701 --> 00:15:12,745
- [HIGH FIVES]
- We both did a good job.

269
00:15:12,828 --> 00:15:14,371
I'm sorry, I'm sorry, I'm sorry.

270
00:15:14,455 --> 00:15:15,831
It's all good. [CLEARS THROAT]

271
00:15:17,124 --> 00:15:18,250
Thanks.

272
00:15:18,334 --> 00:15:19,293
I'll get going.

273
00:15:22,922 --> 00:15:25,007
[FOOTSTEPS RETREATING]

274
00:15:25,090 --> 00:15:27,301
I'm so proud of you, son.

275
00:15:31,513 --> 00:15:32,681
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

276
00:15:33,265 --> 00:15:35,893
I failed to save all of our staff, Ma.

277
00:15:37,019 --> 00:15:38,562
Son,

278
00:15:38,646 --> 00:15:40,564
you couldn't possibly have
saved all of them.

279
00:15:40,648 --> 00:15:42,358
I know that. I know that.

280
00:15:43,484 --> 00:15:45,569
But trust me, I will make sure

281
00:15:47,321 --> 00:15:51,533
that everyone who was involved
in their deaths,

282
00:15:52,701 --> 00:15:55,412
everyone responsible for
what's happening now,

283
00:15:57,498 --> 00:15:58,707
pays the price.

284
00:16:00,125 --> 00:16:02,044
I will make sure they all pay.

285
00:16:09,218 --> 00:16:11,679
Son, your wound.

286
00:16:14,848 --> 00:16:16,225
[GRUNTS]

287
00:16:18,936 --> 00:16:19,937
It's okay.

288
00:16:20,020 --> 00:16:23,232
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

289
00:16:24,024 --> 00:16:25,609
I've already told them

290
00:16:25,693 --> 00:16:27,695
that Lieutenant Areza
is asking for backup.

291
00:16:27,778 --> 00:16:29,196
Thank you, Olsen.

292
00:16:29,279 --> 00:16:31,365
Let's just wait
for the lieutenant's go signal.

293
00:16:31,448 --> 00:16:32,533
Then we'll get out of here.

294
00:16:32,616 --> 00:16:33,742
Okay.

295
00:16:38,998 --> 00:16:41,000
I'm glad, dude.

296
00:16:41,083 --> 00:16:43,085
They're starting to feel happy again.

297
00:16:43,168 --> 00:16:44,503
And hopeful too.

298
00:16:44,586 --> 00:16:46,005
[MELLOW MUSIC PLAYING]

299
00:16:46,088 --> 00:16:47,464
How about you?

300
00:16:47,548 --> 00:16:49,216
Did you also lose hope?

301
00:16:49,299 --> 00:16:50,718
No.

302
00:16:51,635 --> 00:16:53,178
I can't give up.

303
00:16:53,846 --> 00:16:55,014
Exactly.

304
00:16:56,682 --> 00:16:58,058
How about… [CLEARS THROAT]

305
00:16:58,142 --> 00:16:59,184
Liam?

306
00:16:59,268 --> 00:17:00,227
Is he okay now?

307
00:17:01,603 --> 00:17:03,022
He said he's okay now.

308
00:17:03,105 --> 00:17:04,898
But he doesn't look okay to me.

309
00:17:06,984 --> 00:17:11,071
Once the police backup comes,
we can get out of here.

310
00:17:11,155 --> 00:17:12,614
Let's take him to the hospital.

311
00:17:14,616 --> 00:17:15,909
Thank you, dude.

312
00:17:15,993 --> 00:17:17,870
Thank you for looking after him.

313
00:17:18,662 --> 00:17:19,913
I look after everyone.

314
00:17:21,373 --> 00:17:23,000
Don't mention it.

315
00:17:23,083 --> 00:17:25,335
I hope you guys go back
to the way you used to be.

316
00:17:26,420 --> 00:17:27,713
- [STUDENT 1] <i>Criminal's son!</i>
- [STUDENT 2] <i>Criminal's son!</i>

317
00:17:28,422 --> 00:17:29,673
<i>Hey, get back here!</i>

318
00:17:29,757 --> 00:17:31,592
<i>Criminal's son!</i>

319
00:17:31,675 --> 00:17:33,177
[STUDENT 2]<i> Criminal's son!</i>

320
00:17:33,260 --> 00:17:34,344
[STUDENT 1] <i>Criminal's son!</i> [LAUGHS]

321
00:17:34,428 --> 00:17:35,846
[STUDENT 2] <i>Criminal's son!</i> [LAUGHS]

322
00:17:35,929 --> 00:17:37,723
<i>Ooh, criminal's son! </i>[LAUGHS]

323
00:17:37,806 --> 00:17:38,932
<i>Hey, where are you going?</i>

324
00:17:39,016 --> 00:17:40,225
<i>Stay here!</i>

325
00:17:40,309 --> 00:17:42,061
- [GROANS]
<i>- Criminal's son!</i>

326
00:17:42,144 --> 00:17:43,937
<i>Criminal's son!</i>

327
00:17:44,021 --> 00:17:45,314
<i>- Wimp!</i>
<i>- Wimp!</i>

328
00:17:45,397 --> 00:17:46,523
<i>- Wimp!</i>
<i>- Criminal's son!</i>

329
00:17:46,607 --> 00:17:48,442
<i>Hey! Stop that!</i>

330
00:17:48,525 --> 00:17:50,486
<i>You want to get hurt too, huh?</i>

331
00:17:51,070 --> 00:17:52,863
<i>Do you guys want to get expelled?</i>

332
00:17:52,946 --> 00:17:55,449
<i>Feeling cocky, huh?</i>

333
00:17:56,075 --> 00:17:57,534
<i>Hey, what's that?</i>

334
00:17:57,618 --> 00:17:58,660
<i>- Let's go! Run!</i>
<i>- Run!</i>

335
00:17:58,744 --> 00:18:01,288
<i>Who's a wimp now, huh?</i>

336
00:18:12,883 --> 00:18:14,510
<i>Are you all right?</i>

337
00:18:15,094 --> 00:18:17,930
<i>Just tell me if they bother you again.</i>

338
00:18:18,013 --> 00:18:19,431
<i>I got your back.</i>

339
00:18:19,515 --> 00:18:20,974
<i>Thank you, Liam.</i>

340
00:18:24,520 --> 00:18:25,562
<i>Let's go.</i>

341
00:18:27,564 --> 00:18:29,108
[LUNA] Before,

342
00:18:29,191 --> 00:18:32,152
remember, you used to have
each other's back.

343
00:18:32,236 --> 00:18:33,946
That was a long time ago, Luna.

344
00:18:34,029 --> 00:18:35,906
- A long time.
- That's too bad, dude.

345
00:18:35,989 --> 00:18:37,783
- You were like brothers.
- And?

346
00:18:37,866 --> 00:18:40,244
Am I the one who ruined our relationship?

347
00:18:40,327 --> 00:18:41,286
That was him.

348
00:18:41,370 --> 00:18:42,996
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

349
00:18:43,080 --> 00:18:45,040
Then I found out

350
00:18:45,958 --> 00:18:47,626
that his mom is awful.

351
00:18:47,709 --> 00:18:50,003
- She used my mom--
- [LUNA] Olsen.

352
00:18:50,087 --> 00:18:51,380
Please.

353
00:18:51,463 --> 00:18:52,714
Enough of this.

354
00:18:52,798 --> 00:18:58,178
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

355
00:18:58,262 --> 00:18:59,680
[MUSIC FADES]

356
00:19:12,276 --> 00:19:14,820
I'm glad to hear Liam's okay now.

357
00:19:17,739 --> 00:19:18,907
I hope you--

358
00:19:18,991 --> 00:19:21,702
[SORROWFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

359
00:19:21,785 --> 00:19:24,788
I hope you and your wife
can figure things out as well.

360
00:19:26,623 --> 00:19:28,167
Magnus, I don't want…

361
00:19:30,544 --> 00:19:33,589
to get in between you and Greta…

362
00:19:36,091 --> 00:19:38,385
but I hope you don't stay mad at her.

363
00:19:41,972 --> 00:19:44,516
Yes, Greta was wrong for what she did.

364
00:19:47,603 --> 00:19:50,105
But because of what she did,

365
00:19:51,481 --> 00:19:53,817
my son was saved.

366
00:19:55,861 --> 00:19:58,739
Despite all that's happening…

367
00:20:00,782 --> 00:20:02,534
you're still thinking…

368
00:20:04,411 --> 00:20:06,705
of ways for us to be okay again.

369
00:20:10,000 --> 00:20:11,501
If you needed help…

370
00:20:14,755 --> 00:20:16,590
why didn't you come to me?

371
00:20:18,759 --> 00:20:21,386
You know I'd have helped you, right?

372
00:20:23,555 --> 00:20:27,851
So why was I not
the first person you went to for help?

373
00:20:30,979 --> 00:20:33,398
After what happened between us,

374
00:20:34,858 --> 00:20:37,069
how could I ask for your help?

375
00:20:37,736 --> 00:20:39,780
So you asked Greta instead.

376
00:20:46,245 --> 00:20:48,413
That was a mistake.

377
00:20:49,831 --> 00:20:51,208
Well,

378
00:20:53,126 --> 00:20:55,295
if it concerns our children,

379
00:20:56,296 --> 00:20:57,714
we'd know

380
00:20:59,299 --> 00:21:01,176
what's right and wrong.

381
00:21:01,260 --> 00:21:04,012
The thing Greta asked in return…

382
00:21:08,642 --> 00:21:11,228
was going to help your son too.

383
00:21:14,523 --> 00:21:15,983
That's why, Magnus,

384
00:21:17,025 --> 00:21:20,779
I hope you'll stop feeling angry at Greta.

385
00:21:21,530 --> 00:21:23,782
I know you're thinking

386
00:21:25,033 --> 00:21:27,494
that what she did to me was wrong.

387
00:21:31,039 --> 00:21:32,666
But remember,

388
00:21:32,749 --> 00:21:35,252
what I did to her was also wrong.

389
00:21:37,004 --> 00:21:38,839
It wasn't just you.

390
00:21:41,300 --> 00:21:42,634
It was both of us.

391
00:21:57,024 --> 00:21:58,942
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

392
00:22:10,579 --> 00:22:12,289
Greta, what's wrong?

393
00:22:12,372 --> 00:22:17,961
[SORROWFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

394
00:22:20,130 --> 00:22:22,841
- Ice, what's wrong?
- Liam's wound won't stop bleeding.

395
00:22:22,924 --> 00:22:24,718
- What?!
- Come on.

396
00:22:24,801 --> 00:22:25,844
Let's go.

397
00:22:28,096 --> 00:22:29,890
Liam, stop moving.

398
00:22:29,973 --> 00:22:32,809
Your bleeding will increase
if you keep moving.

399
00:22:32,893 --> 00:22:35,270
- [LIAM BREATHING HEAVILY]
- Just keep calm. Okay?

400
00:22:35,353 --> 00:22:38,356
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

401
00:22:38,440 --> 00:22:40,192
[GRUNTS]

402
00:22:41,985 --> 00:22:43,403
Bear with it, son.

403
00:22:43,487 --> 00:22:45,489
- Just bear with it a bit more.
- Ma.

404
00:22:45,572 --> 00:22:47,449
- [GRETA] You've got this.
- [ICE] We're gonna stop the bleeding.

405
00:22:47,532 --> 00:22:49,034
Don't worry.

406
00:22:49,117 --> 00:22:50,577
- I'm right here.
- Okay.

407
00:22:52,496 --> 00:22:54,748
[LIAM GRUNTING IN PAIN]

408
00:23:00,545 --> 00:23:04,758
[LIAM CONTINUES GRUNTING
AND PAINTING]

409
00:23:07,219 --> 00:23:13,892
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

410
00:23:19,147 --> 00:23:20,607
<i>We can go home now?</i>

411
00:23:20,690 --> 00:23:22,442
<i>We'll all go home.</i>

412
00:23:22,526 --> 00:23:25,654
What did you mean when you said
I did something in the past?

413
00:23:25,737 --> 00:23:28,156
<i>You still want to take</i>
<i>my husband away from me!</i>

414
00:23:28,240 --> 00:23:30,075
<i>- That's not true--</i>
<i>- Liar!</i>

415
00:23:30,450 --> 00:23:31,993
<i>Traitor!</i>

416
00:23:32,077 --> 00:23:35,622
<i>This is the first time I've seen Liam</i>
<i>up close. He's pretty cute.</i>

417
00:23:36,206 --> 00:23:37,624
[OLSEN] <i>Don't you have a boyfriend?</i>

418
00:23:38,750 --> 00:23:41,461
<i>After everything we've done so far,</i>
<i>I feel like I can do anything.</i>

419
00:23:41,545 --> 00:23:42,879
<i>You're even capable of forgiveness.</i>

420
00:23:42,963 --> 00:23:46,091
<i>I don't think I can hate her.</i>
<i>I just can't.</i>
